Title: Convex Drawings in Polynomial Area (the open problem continues)  
Author: Michael Goldwasser 
Date: October 20, 1994  
Abstract: This paper analyzes the open problem of whether a graph that emits a convex drawing necessarily emits such a drawing in polynomial area. An exponential lower bound is proven for a series of algorithms based on minimizing what are called `-metrics. Also, this contains a discussion on one possible strategy in designing a polynomial algorithm. 
